Find out more information regarding our For Investors

Connect to the gas network

We’ve got all sorts of things connected to our gas network. Homes, businesses, power stations, even buses!

Click below to find out what you need to know.

  • Connect your home

    We know that setting up a new gas supply can be confusing. So here’s the information you need to apply for and pay for a gas connection for your home.

    There's a few ways you can get a quote for a gas connection. 

    • You can get an Instant Quote for a gas connection here.
    • You can fill in our New Supply online application form with details and we'll send you a quote.
    • You can send us a quick video for a new connection 
    • You can contact us by telephone on 0800 072 6814

    How much will it cost?

    While each connection is slightly different, the costs below is standard for up 10m of work on public land and 20m of work on your land. 

    • If you dig the necessary trenches: £856 excluding VAT
    • If we dig the necessary trenches: £1443 excluding VAT
    • If there is only public land to work on: £769 excluding VAT

    If you’re happy with the price, we’ll need payment as soon as possible, and we’ll contact you within twelve working days to arrange the work. We aim to finish the work and have you on gas within six weeks of you paying for it. 

    Remember we don't install gas meters - you'll have to arrange that with a gas supplier. Once you've paid for your connection, we will give you a Meter Point Reference Number (MPRN) so you can arrange this.

    More?

    You can find out detailed information about connecting to the gas network here. If you are doing some of the work yourself, read about our requirements below:

    • Requirements for Ducting
    • Requirements for Trenching
    • Requirements for multi-utility trench

    If you live in a village that is not on the gas network, we may be able to help you connect too. Call 0800 072 6814 to speak to an advisor (phone lines open Monday - Friday).

  • Connect multiple homes or your business

    To connect multiple domestic properties like a new housing development or a business, it's a slightly different process.  

    Connecting multiple homes or business is just as easy!

    • If you know how much gas you'll be using, you can get an Instant Quote for a business connection here.
    • Alternatively, download and complete this form and and email it to connections@wwutilities.co.uk.

    If you'll be using large amounts of gas, we may need more information from you about the how much gas you're likely to use, and when you'll be using it. To make sure we get it right, we might also need to carry out a feasibility or design study. This will help us come up with the best cost option for you.

    How much will it cost?

    Design fee

    When you request a quote to connect businesses and multiple homes to the gas network, you will be charged a design fee of between £249 and £831 – dependent on your expected gas demand/usage. This reflects the amount of work required to produce detailed design plans.

    Connection cost

    When you’ve paid the design fee, we’ll give you a quote that is valid for 90 days. If you’re happy with the price, we’ll need payment as soon as possible, and we’ll contact you within twelve working days to arrange the work. We aim to finish the work and have you on gas within eight weeks of you paying for it.

    While each connection is slightly different, the costs below are standard for new housing developments with us digging up to 20m on public land and you digging the necessary trenches on your land.

    • 3-10 homes: £1,253 per home excluding VAT
    • 11-100 homes: £991 per home excluding VAT

    Remember we don't install gas meters - you'll have to arrange that with a gas supplier. Once you've paid for your connection, we will give you a Meter Point Reference Number (MPRN) so you can arrange this.

    More

    You can find out more detailed information in our developer's pack. 

    If you are doing some of the work yourself, read about our requirements below:

    • Requirements for Ducting
    • Requirements for Trenching
    • Requirements for multi-utility trench
  • Third Party Connections

    If you’re an Independent Connections Provider (ICP) or an Independent Gas Transporter (IGT) we have a dedicated team who can help you.

    If you are at an early stage of a project and would like basic information on the capacity of the gas network in the area, contact us. We’ll get back to you in five working days.

    For any Third Party Connection enquiry call us on 07977060023 between 8am and 6pm Monday to Friday or email gtuip@wwutilities.co.uk.

Cookies and Privacy

By accessing and using our website you agree to the terms of this policy and our privacy disclaimer. Please read this cookie policy carefully so you know what cookies are used and how. Sadly, we're not talking about biscuits. Cookies are small text files placed on your computer by websites. These files are either stored in the memory of your computer or device or in your web browser. We use cookies to help or personalise your browsing experience and provide information on how you interact with our site so we can make improvements. We respect your right to privacy, therefore you can choose not to allow some types of cookies. Click on the different category headings to find out more and change our default settings. However, blocking some types of cookies may impact your experience of the site and the services we are able to offer.
More information

Manage Cookie Preferences

Strictly Necessary Cookies

Always Active

These cookies are necessary for the website to function and cannot be switched off in our systems. They are usually only set in response to actions made by you which amount to a request for services, such as setting your privacy preferences, logging in or filling in forms. You can set your browser to block or alert you about these cookies, but some parts of the site will not then work. These cookies do not store any personally identifiable information.

Functional Cookies

These cookies enable the website to provide enhanced functionality and personalisation. They may be set by us or by third party providers whose services we have added to our pages. If you do not allow these cookies then some or all of these services may not function properly.

Performance Cookies

These cookies allow us to count visits and traffic sources so we can measure and improve the performance of our site. They help us to know which pages are the most and least popular and see how visitors move around the site. All information these cookies collect is aggregated and therefore anonymous. If you do not allow these cookies we will not know when you have visited our site, and will not be able to monitor its performance.

Social Media Cookies

These cookies are set by a range of social media services that we have added to the site to enable you to share our content with your friends and networks. They are capable of tracking your browser across other sites and building up a profile of your interests. This may impact the content and messages you see on other websites you visit. If you do not allow these cookies you may not be able to use or see these sharing tools.

Targeting Cookies

These cookies may be set through our site by our advertising partners. They may be used by those companies to build a profile of your interests and show you relevant adverts on other sites. They do not store directly personal information, but are based on uniquely identifying your browser and internet device. If you do not allow these cookies, you will experience less targeted advertising.
